About event propagation:
    To send an action up the chain, a property must be set on the component that initiate
    the action. The property must match the string passed as a parameter to sendAction().
    The value of property is the target action for the next handler.

    // component
    'onLoginSuccess': 'actionNameInTheRoute'
    this.sendAction('onLoginSuccess');

    // route
    actions { actionNameInTheRoute() { /* ... /* } }

Alternative: Use https://github.com/DockYard/ember-route-action-helper
{{login-form action=(route-action "actionNameInTheRoute")}}
Invoking the action:  this.sendAction("action")
